issues.title: Turbocharger Failure
issues.description: Multiple reports of premature turbocharger failures, particularly affecting the hot-side turbocharger in the 4.0L twin-turbo V8 engine. Issues include bearing failure, oil leaks, and complete turbo seizure.
issues.fix_description: Complete turbocharger replacement, often requiring engine removal for access
issues.prevention: Regular oil changes with proper grade oil, avoid extended idle periods, allow proper cool-down after spirited driving

issues.title: Carbon Fiber Roof Panel Delamination
issues.description: Carbon fiber roof panels showing signs of delamination and clear coat failure, particularly on edges and high-stress areas. Affects both aesthetic appearance and structural integrity.
symptoms: Visible separation of carbon fiber layers
issues.fix_description: Complete roof panel replacement or professional refinishing
issues.prevention: Regular inspection, avoid parking in direct sunlight for extended periods, use car cover when possible

issues.title: Air Suspension Compressor Failure
issues.description: Adaptive air suspension compressor failures causing the vehicle to drop to lowest setting and inability to raise. Common issue affecting ride height sensors and air lines as well.
issues.fix_description: Replace air suspension compressor and associated components, check for air leaks
issues.prevention: Regular inspection of air lines, avoid overloading vehicle, gentle driving over rough terrain

issues.title: Infotainment System Freezing
issues.description: MMI infotainment system experiencing frequent freezing, black screens, and unresponsive touchscreen functionality. Software updates often provide temporary relief.
issues.fix_description: Software updates, module replacement, or complete infotainment unit replacement
issues.prevention: Keep system software updated, avoid rapid input commands, regular system resets

issues.title: Ceramic Brake Disc Cracking
issues.description: Carbon ceramic brake discs developing cracks, particularly after hard use or extreme temperature cycling. Can lead to catastrophic brake failure if not addressed.
symptoms: Visible cracks on brake disc surface
issues.fix_description: Complete ceramic brake disc replacement, often requires pad replacement as well
issues.prevention: Gradual warm-up of brakes, avoid extreme temperature cycling, regular inspection

issues.title: Fuel Injector Coking
issues.description: Direct injection fuel injectors becoming clogged with carbon deposits, leading to rough idle, misfires, and reduced performance. Common issue with direct injection engines.
issues.fix_description: Fuel injector cleaning or replacement, intake valve cleaning
issues.prevention: Use high-quality fuel, regular fuel system cleaning, occasional high-RPM driving

issues.title: Oil Cooler Line Leaks
issues.description: Engine oil cooler lines developing leaks, particularly at connection points. Can lead to significant oil loss and potential engine damage if not addressed promptly.
issues.fix_description: Replace oil cooler lines and associated seals
issues.prevention: Regular oil level checks, inspect for leaks during maintenance, avoid overheating

issues.title: Transmission Control Module Software Issues
issues.description: 8-speed tiptronic transmission experiencing harsh shifts, delayed engagement, and limp mode due to software calibration issues in the transmission control module.
issues.fix_description: Software update or transmission control module replacement
issues.prevention: Keep software updated, regular transmission service, gentle acceleration patterns

issues.title: Door Handle Sensor Malfunction
issues.description: Electronic door handle sensors failing to detect presence, preventing automatic door unlocking and handle presentation. Affects convenience features.
issues.fix_description: Replace door handle sensor modules and recalibrate system
issues.prevention: Keep sensors clean, avoid excessive moisture exposure, gentle handling

issues.title: Exhaust Valve Actuator Failure
issues.description: Active exhaust valve actuators failing, preventing proper exhaust sound control and potentially affecting engine performance. Common on sport exhaust equipped vehicles.
issues.fix_description: Replace exhaust valve actuators and associated wiring
issues.prevention: Regular system diagnostics, avoid extreme temperature exposure, gentle operation

editorial.tagline: Gran turismo perfection with supercar aggression
editorial.hero_blurb: The RS7 Sportback represents the pinnacle of Audi's gran turismo philosophy, wrapping 591 horsepower in a sleek four-door coupe silhouette. It's the rare machine that can devour autobahn miles in supreme comfort, then unleash fury on a mountain road.
editorial.essence: This is Audi's answer to the question: what if a supercar grew up and got practical? The RS7 combines genuine 200mph capability with everyday usability, all wrapped in one of the most gorgeous bodies ever to wear four rings.
editorial.heritage: Born from Audi's RS legacy that began in 1994 with the RS2 Avant, the RS7 continues the tradition of high-performance family haulers. Building on the A7's swooping sportback design introduced in 2010, the RS variant pushes the envelope with track-bred engineering.
editorial.design_philosophy: Audi's designers sought to create automotive sculpture in motion - a car that looks fast standing still while maintaining the elegance expected of a luxury grand tourer. Every line serves both beauty and aerodynamic function.
editorial.motorsport_history: While not a direct race car derivative, the RS7 benefits from Audi's extensive motorsport experience in DTM, WEC, and Formula E. The quattro all-wheel-drive system traces its DNA to Audi's rally-conquering roots.
editorial.engine_character: The 4.0-liter twin-turbo V8 is a masterpiece of controlled violence - smooth as silk at idle, but transforms into a snarling beast under throttle. It delivers power with the inevitability of a freight train yet maintains refinement that belies its 591-horsepower output.
editorial.transmission_feel: The 8-speed tiptronic transmission is telepathic in automatic mode, disappearing into the background until you need it. Manual mode delivers crisp, decisive shifts that complement the engine's character without the harshness of a DCT.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: The adaptive air suspension and sport differential create a chassis that's simultaneously compliant and precise. It can glide over broken pavement like a luxury sedan, then firm up for canyon carving with sports car tenacity.
editorial.steering_feel: Electrically assisted but naturally weighted, the steering offers excellent road feel without being overly heavy. It's precise enough for spirited driving yet relaxed enough for cross-continental cruising.
editorial.brake_confidence: Massive carbon-ceramic brakes provide fade-free stopping power that matches the engine's fury. Pedal feel is progressive and confidence-inspiring, whether scrubbing speed from triple digits or modulating through city traffic.
editorial.sound_signature: A cultured rumble at idle transforms into a thunderous roar under acceleration, with satisfying pops and crackles on overrun. The exhaust note strikes the perfect balance between sophistication and savagery.
editorial.ideal_owner: The successful professional who needs one car to do everything exceptionally well - someone who values both performance credibility and luxury refinement without compromise.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Pure sports car purists seeking maximum engagement, budget-conscious buyers, or those who prioritize fuel economy over performance capability.
editorial.buyers_summary: Buy for the unparalleled combination of speed, luxury, and practicality that few cars can match. Expect to pay premium prices for premium performance, but know you're getting one of the most complete high-performance machines ever built.
